'''''Tongue of the Fatman''''' (or simply '''''Fatman''''' for the Japan release)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pcgamer.com/saturday-crapshoot-tongue-of-the-fatman/|title=Saturday Crapshoot: Tongue of the Fatman - PC Gamer|last=Cobbett|first=Ricfavorfavorfavorhard|website=[[PC Gamer]] |date=23 September 2011|language=English|accessdate=17 September 2015}}</ref> is a 1989 fighting game developed by [[Activision]] and published by [[Sanritsu]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/games/tongue-of-the-fatman/pc-837329|title=Tongue of the Fatman - PC - IGN|language=English|accessdate=17 September 2015}}</ref>

The game is also renamed by the titles '''''Mondu's Fight Palace''''' on the [[Commodore 64]], and '''''Slaughter Sport''''' in its [[Sega Genesis]] iteration. The working title for the game was 'Red Belt'.

==Overview==

In single-player mode, players begin as any of the 3 races and must take on each of the 10 matches, facing off with each different race from left to right of the given list.<ref name=":1">Rivera, Michael. ''Powerhits Sci/Fi.'' 1992. Pg. 41-56. http://www.mocagh.org/activision/scifipowerhits-manual.pdf<.</ref> Afterwards, they must fight the game's main antagonist: Mondu the Fat, the champion of the fight palace and the last obstacle of the game.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.atarimagazines.com/compute/issue117/p90_reviews3_TONGUE_OF_THE_FATMAN.php|title=Review: Tongue Of The Fatman|last=Netsel|first=Tom|website=www.atarimagazines.com|access-date=2017-11-27}}</ref>

In the Genesis port, single-player mode centers on the player beginning as Rex (or as another fighter through cheat codes) and must take on each of the 8 standard fighters (including their mutant clone) twice, with the second set being the more difficult palette swaps.

==Characters==
The game gives the player ten races to choose from, each race having its own special moves. The original version of the game starts with the player having 3 species to choose from,<ref name=":0">{{Citation|last=Lazy Game Reviews|title=LGR - Tongue of the Fatman - DOS PC Game Review|date=2012-09-21|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qngBXbs3Of0|accessdate=2017-11-26}}</ref> unlocking new characters by defeating them in battle. These 10 races includes:

