''Tongue of the Fatman'' was positively received in its original release, but was looked upon negatively in retrospect. Both [[Game Revolution]] and [[CNET]] ranked it in their list of the worst video game names ever,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamerevolution.com/features/worst_game_names/2|title=The 50 Worst Game Names Ever: Page 2|last=Ferris|first=Duke|date=12 June 2006|language=English|accessdate=17 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cnet.com/news/the-30-dumbest-videogame-titles-ever/|title=The 30 dumbest videogame titles ever - CNET|last=Lanxon|first=Nate|date=18 November 2009|language=English|accessdate=17 September 2015}}</ref> whilst Mondu, the game's antagonist, was ranked among [[UGO]]'s list of the "Unsexiest Sexy Video Game Characters" coming in at number 3.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ugo.com/games/20-unsexiest-sexy-video-game-characters-mondu.html|title=Mondu (Tongue of the Fatman) - 20 Unsexiest Sexy Video Game Characters - UGO.com|last=Meli|first=Marissa|date=27 March 2010|language=English|accessdate=17 September 2015}}</ref> Tongue of the Fatman received a spot in [[PC Gamer]]'s list of the "15 Weirdest PC Games Of All Time", stating that "For raw, eye-popping 'What the crap?!'ery though, you can't do much better than this alien blood sport."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pcgamer.com/the-weirdest-pc-games-of-all-time/|title=The 15 Weirdest PC Games Of All Time - PC Gamer|last=Cobbett|first=Richard|website=PC Gamer|date=5 June 2013|language=English|accessdate=17 September 2015}}</ref>

The editors of ''[[Game Player's PC Strategy Guide]]'' gave ''Tongue of the Fatman'' their 1989 "Best PC Arcade/Action Game" award. They wrote, "Activision's graphics are as wild as ''Fatman''{{'}}s title, and the game play is more than satisfactory.".<ref name=gameplayers1989>{{cite journal | title=''Game Player''{{'}}s First Annual PC Game Awards 1989 | journal=[[Game Player's PC Strategy Guide]] | date=March–April 1990 | volume=3 | number=2 | pages=11, 12 }}</ref>

